 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-207">Die Suche erfolgt anhand der Objekte, die durch den distinguished Name, die im Attribut des Basisobjekts angegeben wird, identifiziert werden.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-207">The search is performed against the objects that are identified by the distinguished name that is specified in the attribute of the base object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="30ced-208">Beispielsweise ist das Basisobjekt eine Adschema Gruppe-Klasse und die <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> nastaven NA hodnotu "Member", und klicken Sie dann die Suche für alle Objekte ausgeführt wird, die Mitglieder der Gruppe sind.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-208">For example, if the base object is an adschema group class and the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> is set to "member," then the search will be performed against all objects that are members of the group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="30ced-209">Weitere Informationen finden Sie im Thema Adschema "Group"-Klasse, in der MSDN Library unter [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-209">For more information, see the adschema "Group" class topic in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-210">Wenn die <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> Eigenschaft wird verwendet, die <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> Eigenschaft muss festgelegt werden, um <xref:System.DirectoryServices.SearchScope.Base>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-210">When the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property is used, the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> property must be set to <xref:System.DirectoryServices.SearchScope.Base>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="30ced-211">Wenn die <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> -Eigenschaftensatz auf einem anderen Wert festlegen die <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> Eigenschaft löst eine <xref:System.ArgumentException>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-211">If the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> property is set to any other value, setting the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property will throw an <xref:System.ArgumentException>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-212">Weitere Informationen finden Sie im Thema "Ausführen einer Attribute Scope-Query" in der MSDN Library unter [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library)).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-212">For more information, see the "Performing an Attribute Scope Query" topic in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library)).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-213">Das folgende Beispiel zeigt, wie Sie mit der <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> Eigenschaft mit dem das Member-Attribut zum Abrufen der Mitglieder einer Gruppe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-213">The following example shows how to use the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property with the member attribute to get the members of a group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="30ced-214">Klicken Sie dann die vor- und Nachnamen-Namen, der die Elemente und ihre Telefonnummern ausgegeben.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-214">It then prints out the first and last names of the members and their telephone numbers.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
DirectoryEntry group = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=MyGroup, …");  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher(group "(&(objectClass=user)(objectCategory=Person))");  
src.AttributeScopedQuery = "member";  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("sn");  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("givenName");  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("telephoneNumber");  
foreach(SearchResult res in src.FindAll())  
{  
    Console.WriteLine("…");  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-232">Im folgende C#-Beispiel veranschaulicht die legen Sie die <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.DerefAlias%2A> Eigenschaft <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DereferenceAlias.Always> , sodass es Aliase dereferenziert, wenn sowohl Suchen der untergeordneten Elemente, und Suchen von Objekten basieren.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-232">The following C# example shows how to set the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.DerefAlias%2A> property to <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DereferenceAlias.Always> , so that it dereferences aliases when both searching subordinates and locating base objects.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
// Bind to the users container.  
DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=users,DC=fabrikam,DC=com");  
// Create a DirectorySearcher object.  
DirectorySearcher mySearcher = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
// Set DerefAlias to Always.  
src.DerefAlias = DerefenceAlias.Always;  
//Use the FindAll method to get search results.  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-242">Das folgende Beispiel zeigt, wie eine Auflistung von distinguished Names im Hexadezimalformat zurückgegeben wird.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-242">The following example shows how to return a collection of distinguished names in hexadecimal format.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.ExtendedDN = ExtendedDN.HexString;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-303">Wenn <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchRoot%2A> ist ein null-Verweis (`Nothing` in Visual Basic), der Suchstamm auf den Stamm der Domäne, die vom Server derzeit verwendeten festgelegt ist.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-303">If <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchRoot%2A> is a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic), the search root is set to the root of the domain that your server is currently using.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="30ced-304">Es gibt mehrere Möglichkeiten, die in den globalen Katalog gesucht werden soll:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-304">There are several ways to search in the global catalog:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="30ced-305">Auflisten Sie des globalen Katalogs ein, und wählen Sie das erste untergeordnete Element.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-305">Enumerate the global catalog and pick the first child.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="30ced-306">Geben Sie den Servernamen an.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-306">Specify the server name.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="30ced-307">Verwenden Sie die DsGetDcName-Funktion, um den globalen Katalog zu suchen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-307">Use the DsGetDcName function to find the global catalog.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="30ced-308">Weitere Informationen über die DsGetDcName-Funktion finden Sie im Thema "DsGetDcName" in der MSDN Library unter [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-308">For more information on the DsGetDcName function, see the topic "DsGetDcName" in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="30ced-309">Rufen Sie den RootDSE des globalen Katalogs ein, und fordern Sie "RootNamingContext".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-309">Get the RootDSE  of the global catalog and ask for "rootNamingContext".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="30ced-310">Verwenden Sie den globalen Katalog, einen Suchpfad angeben, wie bei der Verwendung von LDAP.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-310">Use the global catalog, specifying a search path as if using LDAP.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="30ced-311">Z. B. "GC: / / OU =..., DC =..., DC =...".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-311">For example, "GC://OU=..., DC=..., DC=...".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="30ced-312">Der folgende C#-Code veranschaulicht das Auflisten des globalen Katalogs ein, und wählen Sie das erste untergeordnete Element.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="30ced-312">The following C# code shows how to enumerate the global catalog and pick the first child.</span></span>  
  
    ```csharp  
    DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("GC://forestname");  
    IEnumerator ie = entry.Children.GetEnumerator();  
    ie.MoveNext();  
    entry = (DirectoryEntry)ie.Current;  
    DirectorySearcher search = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
    ```

  
  
## Examples  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.SecurityMasks = SecurityMasks.Dacl | SecurityMasks.Owner;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
